
SET SERVEROUTPUT ON;
DECLARE
num1 NUMBER := 10;
num2 NUMBER := 20;
sum NUMBER;
BEGIN
sum := num1 + num2;
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('The sum of ' || num1 || ' and ' || num2 || ' is: ' || sum);
END;
/


This PL/SQL block declares two variables num1 and num2 initialized with the values 10 and 20 
respectively. It then calculates the sum of num1 and num2 and stores it in the sum variable. Finally, it 
uses the DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE procedure to display the result.


Sample Output:
The sum of 10 and 20 is: 30
